      <div class="section">
        <h2>Welcome!</h2>
        <p>
          Deepfake awareness means understanding that audio, images, and videos can now be convincingly faked using artificial intelligence, and learning how to question what is seen and heard online. It encourages people to look for warning signs such as unusual eye movements, mismatched lighting, distorted voices, or inconsistent background details, and to verify content through trusted sources before sharing it. By increasing awareness, individuals become better prepared to spot scams, misinformation, and abuse that rely on deepfake technology, helping to protect themselves and others in the digital world.
        </p>
        <a href="protection.html"><img src="images/awareness.jpeg" alt="AI Awareness" class="centered-img"></a>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>Digital Safety</h2>
        <p>
          Digital safety in the UK is guided by the Online Safety Act, which aims to protect both children and adults from harmful and illegal online content. Under this law, companies must block or remove dangerous material, enforce age verification to shield young people from inappropriate content, and provide clear reporting tools for users to flag problems. These protection policies help keep digital spaces safe and encourage responsible online behaviour, while empowering users to navigate the internet with greater confidence. Click on the picture below to get broader information for UK protection policies.
        </p>
        <a href="protection.html"><img src="images/safety.webp" alt="Deepfake Example" class="centered-img"></a>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
        <h2>Deepfake Detection</h2>
        <p>
          Detecting deepfakes involves using advanced AI tools and forensic techniques to identify manipulated audio, images, and videos. These systems analyze subtle inconsistencies such as unnatural eye movements, lip-sync mismatches, lighting anomalies, and voice tone variations to determine authenticity. Leading detection methods include deep learning algorithms, biometric analysis, and real-time monitoring platforms, which help organizations, journalists, and individuals spot and prevent digital deception in an era of rapidly evolving AI threats. For more information and practical tips on deepfake detection, please click on the picture below.
        </p>
        <a href="news.html"><img src="images/detectai2.png" alt="Digital Safety" class="centered-img"></a>
      </div>
      <div class="section">
